---

## 🔍 Methodology

### 1. Exploratory Analysis

* Time series visualization
* Descriptive statistics
* Seasonal boxplots
* Additive and multiplicative decomposition
* Autocorrelation analysis (ACF)
* Augmented Dickey-Fuller (ADF) stationarity test

### 2. Trend & Seasonality Modeling

* Linear trend estimation
* Seasonal harmonic terms (sine/cosine)
* Model selection using:

  * Adjusted R²
  * AIC

### 3. ARIMA Modeling

* Automatic model identification using:

```r
auto.arima(seasonal = TRUE, stepwise = FALSE)
```

* Residual diagnostics
* Ljung-Box test
* Forecast generation for 24 months

---

## 📈 Results

### 🔥 Industrial Gas Production

| Metric      | Value                   |
| ----------- | ----------------------- |
| Trend       | Increasing              |
| Seasonality | Winter & Summer Peaks   |
| Model Type  | Additive                |
| Adjusted R² | 0.854                   |
| ARIMA Model | ARIMA(0,1,3)(0,1,1)[12] |
| AIC         | 1942.08                 |
| RMSE        | 2.65                    |

---

### 🌿 Garden Equipment Sales

| Metric      | Value                              |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Trend       | Strongly Increasing                |
| Seasonality | Spring Peak                        |
| Model Type  | Multiplicative                     |
| Adjusted R² | 0.879                              |
| ARIMA Model | ARIMA(3,0,0)(0,1,2)[12] with drift |
| AIC         | 6311.34                            |
| RMSE        | 1046.71                            |

---

## ⚖️ Comparative Analysis

| Criterion        | Gas Production        | Garden Equipment Sales |
| ---------------- | --------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Trend            | Increasing            | Strongly Increasing    |
| Seasonality      | Winter & Summer Peaks | Spring Peak            |
| Seasonality Type | Additive              | Multiplicative         |
| Differencing     | d=1, D=1              | d=1, D=1               |
| Best ARIMA       | (0,1,3)(0,1,1)[12]    | (3,0,0)(0,1,2)[12]     |
| Adjusted R²      | 0.854                 | 0.879                  |

### Key Findings

* Both series exhibit strong annual seasonality (s = 12).
* Both are non-stationary in their original form.
* Gas production presents a relatively constant seasonal amplitude (additive structure).
* Garden equipment sales display increasing seasonal variability over time (multiplicative structure).
---


## ⭐ Conclusion

This project demonstrates the application of classical time series techniques, including decomposition, stationarity testing, ARIMA modeling, and forecasting. The results highlight the importance of understanding trend and seasonal structures before building predictive models.
